@page "/render-foreach"
<PageTitle>Render &amp; Foreach - Saascade Docs</PageTitle>

<h1 id="render-foreach">Render &amp; Foreach</h1>

<div class="doc-layout">

<main class="documentation">

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="render">Render</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                The Render component is a utility for conditionally rendering content
                without introducing extra DOM elements.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <pre><code>&lt;Render&gt;
    @@ChildContent
&lt;/Render&gt;</code></pre>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="foreach">Foreach</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                The Foreach component iterates over a collection and renders a template
                for each item — a declarative alternative to @@foreach in Razor markup.
            </p>

            <pre><code>&lt;Foreach Items="items" Context="item"&gt;
    &lt;Li&gt;@@item.Name&lt;/Li&gt;
&lt;/Foreach&gt;</code></pre>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="listof">ListOf</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                The ListOf component renders a typed list of items, combining iteration
                with list-specific rendering logic.
            </p>

            <pre><code>&lt;ListOf Items="products" Context="product"&gt;
    &lt;Card&gt;
        &lt;CardTitle&gt;@@product.Name&lt;/CardTitle&gt;
    &lt;/Card&gt;
&lt;/ListOf&gt;</code></pre>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="bootstrap">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="render-foreach-bootstrap">Bootstrap 5 Render &amp; Foreach</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Bootstrap 5 Render &amp; Foreach</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                When using Foreach or ListOf with Bootstrap 5, the child components inside the
                template receive Bootstrap class names through the active design system. A Foreach
                that renders Li elements will produce list-group-item styled items if the parent
                Ul is given the appropriate specialization. The iteration logic is completely
                framework-agnostic — only the resolved class names differ.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="daisyui">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="render-foreach-daisyui">DaisyUI Render &amp; Foreach</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">DaisyUI Render &amp; Foreach</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                When using Foreach or ListOf with DaisyUI, child components inside the template
                automatically receive DaisyUI semantic class names. A Foreach rendering Card
                components inside a CardsGrid produces a responsive card layout styled with
                DaisyUI's card and bg-base-100 classes. The data binding and rendering pipeline
                is identical regardless of the active design system.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="basecoat">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="render-foreach-basecoat">Basecoat Render &amp; Foreach</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Basecoat Render &amp; Foreach</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                When using Foreach or ListOf with Basecoat, child components inside the template
                receive Basecoat's utility-first Tailwind class compositions. The template
                body is written once and renders correctly regardless of whether Bootstrap,
                DaisyUI, or Basecoat is the active design system — making Foreach and ListOf
                ideal for building reusable data-driven UI patterns.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

</main>

<TableOfContents Items="@([
    new TocItem("render-foreach", "Render & Foreach"),
    new TocItem("render", "Render", 2),
    new TocItem("foreach", "Foreach", 2),
    new TocItem("listof", "ListOf", 2),
    new TocItem("render-foreach-bootstrap", "Bootstrap 5", 2),
    new TocItem("render-foreach-daisyui", "DaisyUI", 2),
    new TocItem("render-foreach-basecoat", "Basecoat", 2)
])" />

</div>
